{"PARUMBILICAL":[{"def":"Near the umbilicus; -- applied especially to one or more small veins which, in man, connect the portal vein with the epigastric veins in the front wall of the abdomen.","pos":""}],"PARURE":[{"def":"An ornament or decoration for the person; esp.","pos":""}],"PARUSIA":[{"def":"A figure of speech by which the present tense is used instead of the past or the future, as in the animated narration of past, or in the prediction of future, events.","pos":""}]}